  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Interior Designer (Architectural, minor M&E",
  "description": "<p></p><ul><li>Production of scaled site plans and as built drawings (Architectural / minor M&E)</li><li>Production of detailed, shop and construction drawings</li><li>Liaison between supporting vendors together with Senior Designer / Creative Director from project commencement to completion</li><li>Compilation of completed as built drawings</li><li>Develop and prepare drawings and designs from sketches, specification sheets</li><li>Ensure timely completion with project team members</li><li>Attend site meetings /conduct site measurements for drawings production</li><li>Perform any other duties and responsibilities as may be assigned from time to time</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Min of 5 years and proficient in AutoCAD, SketchUp, Revit and other modelling software or programs.</li><li>Knowledge and experience of UD and BCA requirements advantageous</li><li>Experienced with interior decoration, finishing materials, furnishing, accessories and artwork.</li><li>Ergonomics design / drafting standards advantageous</li><li>Nitec/ITC/Diploma/Degree in related field (Architectural / Engineering / Civil)</li><li>Exceptional communicator</li><li>Team player, self motivated, able to work independently</li><li>Good interpersonal and people management skills</li></ul><p><strong>Company profile</strong></p><p>ID.Inc Interiors Pte Ltd</p><p>Architectural & Design Services11-50 employees</p><p>ID.inc. is a regional interior design firm specialising in offering intelligent solutions for the corporate sector. Headquartered in Singapore we have regional experience across Asia including Malaysia, Thailand, and Hong Kong- and have undertaken projects up to 50,000 sq ft in size.</p>",
